N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 10 ยง 441.265 - Prepay

State Regulations

To pay for a service before its receipt or enjoyment; such prepayment, as for insurance or rent, reflecting long-established
commercial practices, contrasts with accrue (or the recognition of the receipt
or enjoyment of other types of services paid for after their receipt or
enjoyment). Notes
